        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 5:39PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 538 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Verona, or 32 miles northeast of Ellendale, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Verona.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
